# UI Aesthetics & UX Paradigms

Visual design rules for rendered UI. Pairs with `ui_requirements.instructions.md` and `ui_code.instructions.md`.

## Default Look

| Property | Default |
|---|---|
| Background | Low-key dark gray (~`#1e1e22`–`#2a2a2e`), never pure black |
| Text | Light on dark; muted greys for secondary |
| Accent | Single subtle accent hue per theme |
| Mood | Easy on the eyes; minimal contrast except for hierarchy |

Resolve values via **theme palette semantic tokens** — never hardcode hex in widgets.

## Region Separation

| Do | Don't |
|---|---|
| Subtle fill differences (`surface_base` vs `surface_raised`) | Stack borders inside borders |
| One thin separator when fill change isn't enough | Heavy frames around every group |
| Padding/spacing for grouping | Decorative dividers |

Prefer fill → spacing → 1px separator → border.

## Layout Density

- Minimal, clean, dense; avoid unnecessary padding in nested widgets
- Max ~3 visual container nesting depths; flatten beyond that
- Borders 1–2 px; avoid heavy rounded corners in dense layouts
- Whitespace > chrome

## Typography

- Hierarchy via size/weight/color tokens, not decorative boxes
- Monospace only for code, paths, numeric debug readouts

## Motion

- Short transitions (≤150 ms) for hover/focus; respect reduced-motion OS settings
